==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trimethylamine
<hw>Tri*meth`yl*am"ine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Trimethyl-</ets> + <ets>amine</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A colorless volatile alkaline liquid,
<chform>N.(CH3)3</chform>, obtained from herring brine, beet roots,
etc., with a characteristic herringlike odor. It is regarded as a
substituted ammonia containing three methyl groups.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trimethylene</ent>⟦br⟧
